<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/index.php?title=Springblossom&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1" title="Edit section: Overview">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline" id="Overview">Overview</span></h2>
<p>The fastest M6 in the known universe, the Springblossom also mounts very heavy weaponry and comes at a knock-down price. A, if not the, favourite Corvette class ship.
</p>
<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/index.php?title=Springblossom&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2" title="Edit section: Background">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline" id="Background">Background</span></h2>
<p>The Springblossom class was originally a derivation of the Winterblossom design used to first explore the gate network. This version seems to be modified for other uses besides exploration.
</p>
<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/index.php?title=Springblossom&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3" title="Edit section: Physical Characteristics">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline" id="Physical_Characteristics">Physical Characteristics</span></h2>
<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/index.php?title=Springblossom&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4" title="Edit section: Combat">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline" id="Combat"> Combat </span></h2>
<p>The Springblossom is quick enough to strike an enemy and withdraw without the opponent's turrets ever even being brought to bear. By this point, it is too late for most opponents, and nearly too late for the rest.
</p><p>When equipped with the <a href="/index.php/Prototype_Starburst_Shockwave_Cannon" title="Prototype Starburst Shockwave Cannon">Prototype Starburst Shockwave Cannon</a> in all turrets, the Springblossom commits genocide against fighters, even though it struggles to source the energy to fire them.
</p>
<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/index.php?title=Springblossom&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5" title="Edit section: Equipment">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline" id="Equipment"> Equipment </span></h2>
<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/index.php?title=Springblossom&amp;action=edit&amp;section=6" title="Edit section: Availability">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline" id="Availability"> Availability </span></h2>
<p>The Springblossom becomes available to you during the <a href="/index.php/Terran_plot" title="Terran plot">Terran plot</a>, after you enter the lost sector <a href="/index.php/Aldrin" title="Aldrin">Aldrin</a>.
</p>
<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/index.php?title=Springblossom&amp;action=edit&amp;section=7" title="Edit section: Suggested Roles">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline" id="Suggested_Roles"> Suggested Roles</span></h2>
<p>Good as a player ship, the Springblossom's speed and fighter-raping prowess make it the perfect choice for a rapid response unit, jumping into Sectors where your assests are under attack and quickly neutralising every threat in the Sector.
The Springblossom is also an excellent taxi, especially with  with the bonus pack afterburner. This is an ideal way to raise your Terran rank, as speed is vastly more useful then anything else in Terran space, and the Springblossom has the cargo space to handle large taxi runs and still run the afterburner.
</p>
